cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new vehicular network architecture integrated with 5G mobile communication technologies and software defined network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper analyzes the transmission delay and throughput of the proposed network. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as security is an important aspect of vehicular networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of fog cells to cover vehicles and avoid frequent handovers. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper may touch on the societal impact of intelligent transportation systems.
